Colombian Stocks: Corp. Financiera Colombiana, Petrominerales

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-09T16:54:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/colombian-stocks-corp-financiera-colombiana-petrominerales.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:56 a.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.7 percent to 13,425.16, while the
Colcap Index dropped 0.8 percent to 1,631.81.  Corp. Financiera Colombiana SA (CORFICOL CB), the
financial-services and holding company with investments in the
 construction industry , rose 1.1 percent to 35,400 pesos.  Empresas Copec SA, Chile’s largest forestry company, agreed
to buy a 7.85 percent stake in Sociedad de Inversiones en
Energia SA from Corficolombiana, as the company is known, at
12,700 pesos each for a total of 184 billion pesos ($102
million).  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based  oil company 
with production and exploration in  Colombia , fell 2.3 percent to
56,300 pesos. The company, government officials and local
residents will hold a meeting Sept. 9 aimed at ending a protest
that cut the company’s Colombian oil production, Portafolio
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  